    "CGAL::Compute_cone_boundaries_2": {
      "kind": "class",
      "name": "CGAL::Compute_cone_boundaries_2",
      "brief": "The functor for computing the directions of cone boundaries with a given cone number and a given initial direction.",
      "detailed": "This computation can be either inexact by simply dividing an approximate $ \\pi $ by the cone number (which is quick), or exact by using roots of polynomials (requiring number types such as CORE::Expr or leda_real , which are slow). The inexact computation is done by the general functor definition, while the exact computation is done by a specialization of this functor. In the construction of cone-based spanners such as Yao graph and Theta graph implemented by this package, this functor is called first to compute the cone boundaries. Of course, this functor can also be used in other applications where the plane needs to be divided into equally-angled cones. Traits_ Must be either CGAL::Exact_predicates_exact_constructions_kernel_with_root_of or CGAL::Exact_predicates_inexact_constructions_kernel .",
